Louis: "Huh, I won."1
Hilda: "Well, what will it be?"1
Louis: "Give me ten dollars."1
Hilda: "That's gambling and gambling is illegal. Do you want to go to prison?"1
Louis: "Gee, fine... Then maybe I'll just hold it over your head until\you least expect it."1
Hilda: "Nope, you have to use it in a day or the privilege'll expire."1
Louis: "Where'd all these conditionals come from?"1
Hilda: "The rules must change as new situations present\themselves. It's called judge-centered law-making."1
Louis: "That's an interesting way to say you made them up."1
